pr_review_comments: [{'comment_id': 1301625750, 'comment_body': 'This should be fetched from the `[shared]` section, so you can remove it.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 8, 22, 13, 10, 30, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'javfg', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1301626706, 'comment_body': 'This is part of our change to generate notifications on all uploads, so you can remove it.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 8, 22, 13, 11, 12, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'javfg', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1301628175, 'comment_body': 'It would be better to return `err` or a new error with the status code.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 8, 22, 13, 12, 22, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'javfg', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1301638183, 'comment_body': 'You should use camelCase, not snake_case.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 8, 22, 13, 19, 47, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'javfg', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1301647971, 'comment_body': 'You can query for a single row, take a look [here](https://github.com/javfg/reva/blob/a80dc6ffc4d4e31f5218933ab8d9d6a58956faf8/pkg/cbox/preferences/sql/sql.go#L93).', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 8, 22, 13, 26, 42, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'javfg', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1303999423, 'comment_body': 'It would be better to return `nil, err` and change the return type to `(*bool, error)`, you can even do the boolean parsing in this method.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 8, 24, 8, 38, 50, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'javfg', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1304007944, 'comment_body': "I'd say it's better not to return an error when there are no rows, right? If there are no rows, we must assume the user has never enabled the 'Disable notifications' checkbox and so `disableNotifications` would be `False`.", 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 8, 24, 8, 45, 45, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'javfg', 'type': 'User'}]
